<paragraph blockId="12.[125,1172,1346,1498]" pageId="12" pageNumber="2730">
My specimens fit the redescription of this species (
<bibRefCitation author="Bertolani R &amp; Rebecchi L" box="[739,1095,1346,1370]" pageId="12" pageNumber="2730" pagination="127 - 152" refId="ref5680" refString="Bertolani R, Rebecchi L. 1993. A revision of the Macrobiotus hufelandi group (Tardigrada, Macrobiotidae), with some observations on the taxonomic characters of eutardigrades. Zoologica Scripta 22: 127 - 152." type="journal article" year="1993">Bertolani and Rebecchi 1993</bibRefCitation>
). This species was reported as a new record for 
<collectingCountry box="[640,711,1378,1402]" name="China" pageId="12" pageNumber="2730">China</collectingCountry>
from 
<collectingRegion box="[792,872,1378,1402]" country="China" name="Beijing" pageId="12" pageNumber="2730">Beijing</collectingRegion>
Municipality and 
<collectingRegion country="China" name="Hebei" pageId="12" pageNumber="2730">Hebei Province</collectingRegion>
(Rahm 1936â€“1937a). It was subsequently collected from 
<collectingRegion box="[923,1172,1410,1434]" country="China" name="Guangdong" pageId="12" pageNumber="2730">Guangdong Province</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Mathews GB" box="[133,312,1442,1466]" pageId="12" pageNumber="2730" pagination="32 - 35" refId="ref6314" refString="Mathews GB. 1937. More tardigrades from the Far East. China Journal 27: 32 - 35." type="journal article" year="1937">Mathews 1937</bibRefCitation>
) and from 
<collectingRegion box="[453,638,1442,1466]" country="China" name="Nei Mongol" pageId="12" pageNumber="2730">Inner Mongolia</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[703,843,1442,1466]" name="Hong Kong" pageId="12" pageNumber="2730">Hong Kong</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Pilato G" box="[862,1007,1442,1466]" pageId="12" pageNumber="2730" pagination="59 - 68" refId="ref6365" refString="Pilato G. 1974. Tre nuove specie di Tardigradi muscicoli di Cina. Animalia 1: 59 - 68." type="journal article" year="1974">Pilato 1974</bibRefCitation>
). It has never been reported from the Tsinling Mountains.
</paragraph>
